[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring module loading issues**\n\nI’m considering module-info and potential issues with the jar tool, like the InvalidModuleDescriptorException. If the module descriptor exports an existing package, it should be fine, right? \n\nI think testing if the module layer can handle the modelmapper module is key. It seems like there might be complexities with the classloader and native images. If things aren't set up correctly, could it lead to exceptions? I’m not totally sure about the limitations either, but dynamic loading sounds challenging here.\n\n**Clarifying dynamic class loading issues**\n\nI’m trying to figure out the class writing process after the image build. The instructions say to catch unsupported errors, but I'm wondering if native might actually fail with a ClassNotFoundException instead of an Error. Existing tests seem to only catch Errors—which isn’t helpful.\n\nIf the fake Installer isn’t included in the native build, then the test’s runtime behavior could lead to an UnsupportedFeatureError. It seems crucial to ensure that native behavior aligns with the dynamic class loading pattern outlined in the instructions.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc21842f0c819fa42dd90754421cd8\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_CGT8naOWTyUkbtjY1wcc2KZJbyIwSjvqdX8gAzNU-j-jd86EpZwCCKab_fUn9fKt30KP68hvcnF766IDzV8yYmIWncV9eKRC70LMXK3EeyjuI3aMcmM4A3-eXGS1rjxMshS9U4b23ORtVkYdCjnjhjHxUGIIr9GZKvP7y6oHfE_8z0FGC1DXFkp6212zz3s08k5tNdWwwMtb2ukfeWvxds7fn227WpPNCSNI5ZyjhzIFLbOXnA8ftr7EwdYnXFsvqpKUrZ3S4NfI_EB7v9JiMZh9LMk6MHD0lbjxzNZgpdUuAIA7pzHxN9gBjN2WSQg3gqI15VJhYSJeXUhkI9x0r9tBEAFLYSuMi58MdEPwRotZraI-MEmoDEixe8efgIfR6CcOpvCe8PDnMdGNpxkwGfxhKsVUrqGnHlrp-qJVCrF3rI7YtJfvmBlpwngB_JYfWq5g-Swr77IZnXCcVDbRamzadLc9p5pN5GcTrVWSkltpUYiXcxaKxDH1slvEGwiVC1rmv97JmwAujHzwMLcOyEtQ8AyxyporlGHkcZdK2yyvwzpt8BDKCxoncKFpRqBe7zKX7CDLOMtyd7i4QEdVaa