ing about verifying the execution process for compilation or running in a standalone context. I think it might not need test cases, but I'm not certain. If `Module.canRead` returns false for named versus unnamed, that could trigger a branch to execute. I wonder if the target is not unnamed but is actually the same modelmapper module. Also, how would a fake Installer load into the modelmapper module? I need to think this through.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m considering if we can adapt the Installer class to return a class from a named module when it's unread by the source. It seems that the ClassLoader's loadClass method is virtual in the system loader, so I can't intercept it directly. However, I wonder if we have the ability to set the system class loader using `java.system.class.loader` during startup. It's an interesting technical challenge I’m trying to navigate!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NaXvfoQjepwuj5tYNG2cEJc8|fc_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc22bae828819fbd88a3977d51fb1e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap java.lang.ModuleLayer | sed -n '1,160p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2410, "output": 1728, "cacheRead": 61440, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 65578, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778131615043, "responseId": "resp_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc22a05a5c819fb45f8cbe835ea69b"}}
