e `installerClassBytes`, or is there a benefit for jar creation? Also, we might not need to catch `ClassNotFound`. Let's tweak the approach!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ijDPNSiL6n3XzvGQH8ON2yvS|fc_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc23880978819faf0087223f3f17c5", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d)\nmkdir -p \"$tmp/src/org.modelmapper.agentbuilder.installer/org/modelmapper/internal/bytebuddy/agent\"\ncat > \"$tmp/src/org.modelmapper.agentbuilder.installer/module-info.java\" <<'EOF'\nmodule org.modelmapper.agentbuilder.installer {\n    requires java.instrument;\n    exports org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.agent;\n}\nEOF\ncat > \"$tmp/src/org.modelmapper.agentbuilder.installer/org/modelmapper/internal/bytebuddy/agent/Installer.java\" <<'EOF'\npackage org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.agent;\n\nimport java.lang.instrument.Instrumentation;\n\npublic final class Installer {\n    private Installer() {\n    }\n\n    public static Instrumentation getInstrumentation() {\n        return null;\n    }\n}\nEOF\njavac --release 21 -d \"$tmp/out\" $(find \"$tmp/src\" -name '*.java')\nbase64 -w0 \"$tmp/out/module-info.class\" > /tmp/installer_module.b64\nbase64 -w0 \"$tmp/out/org/modelmapper/internal/bytebuddy/agent/Installer.class\" > /tmp/installer_cls.b64\nwc -c /tmp/installer_module.b64 /tmp/installer_cls.b64\ncat /tmp/installer_module.b64\nprintf '\\n---\\n'\ncat /tmp/installer_cls.b64\n", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1935, "output": 1624, "cacheRead": 71680, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 75239, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778131823826, "responseId": "resp_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc23727654819fb5ded6227e170152"}}
