[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing JVM Classpath Issues**\n\nI’m thinking about the test JVM classpath, which may include the build/classes directory after deletion, but not the jar. I wonder if compileTestJava doesn’t delete the output if the source is removed, meaning stale classes might stick around from previous compilations. Since we didn't have the Java source for Installer, it was created at runtime in the last test run. If the Gradle process loaded it before deletion, I’m curious how that might affect things. Maybe I should generate a driver to choose ModuleLayer.boot() for clarity!\n\n**Verifying class loading behavior**\n\nI’m considering whether to use the target module instead of the system loader. The ClassLoader can't seem to load classes from child or module layers with the platform parent, but it can load named modules that are explicitly defined. Since modules defined under the same class loader can read each other, it seems logical to test this with a small experiment. I'll compile modules A and B under the same class loader to check if they can read each other.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_01e59afe7f0611f70169fc23d061d0819fae35fa9c81b96354\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_CPkb2ff_BtNcMLGZvOm1pG_NTRI5c0oqabqmuiQQJTkjn3v6TTXmbGQvv3yiaG2U8WaKmT2Gzljkzv0Vt1wMeBDFKjl9EKZaXh5DyU7KA6GUKrTGQ8G3sqbXAwnQlt5hOwIDYTpewOW7pZvWzrfajf5-6pd61k_UEydP4rFz3NaPHfxqsBt3K5MsuvkZ30Qb6bpe53m9L4W1ywmJty7BawnNNjGu1ETyyrHNSsWdl9hxzl998Z6BoUZVZp6ZzRhHgg6erMhoQtE2g8viUX-x3au81XJKrBQdss1_8r-6iyRn7cb8LBHmX_S1JN-wDPHqG4r-bDrefjCAuobexMgLUY0RccmPTPD12nj2_AajSZSp2pgWiWinEW9pF91DWsL1BfpSaLygzCENwYg3YXkEQgvXS6Rf9T-pfQQTcdKglcB9T_aeyfLskpWng_h-pfprYd1cxlAT5Xo8liBLWnI3Z9J1tX4uixa025Btg1Cd_vdzgFvSJTjM0A4-a0Wt-AbjevjcLauQSvRaEPrMa4rJwlDSfAkVHhlqyT1RiE0C9_IHeFQ9SNdOXEmrtsSIoovpr4dGHt1aE7t15m0qzI6kG6BU5cvfUOsixpJSbZVdQhPpZo2wFcddl_alrvETjd9A5sP7HGh7c91jpG59mcWqvqzLPyONWPxDk